# Gridiron Developer Department — root environment overview.
# This is a two-runtime monorepo: a Python FastAPI backend and a Next.js
# frontend. Each has its own env file — copy and fill in both:
#
#   backend/.env.example  → backend/.env       (Python backend — required)
#   apps/web/.env.example → apps/web/.env.local (Next.js frontend)
#
# Never commit .env* files — enforced by .gitignore.
#
# Quick start (local dev, matches docker-compose.yml):
#   1. docker compose up -d          # Postgres + pgvector
#   2. cp backend/.env.example backend/.env    # then fill in ANTHROPIC_API_KEY etc.
#   3. cp apps/web/.env.example apps/web/.env.local
#
# See backend/.env.example for the full list of ~85 backend variables
# (models, cost controls, RBAC, credential vault, rate limiting, etc.)
# and docs/DEPLOYMENT.md for production deployment notes.
